==Swedish==
===Adverb===
'''lagom'''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPAchar|/ˈlaːˌgom/}} {{Audio|sv-lagom.ogg|Audio}}
#(just) right, [[fitting]], neither too much or too little
#:''Vi har skaffat en '''lagom''' dyr bil.''
#:"We've bought a car that's just the right price."

====Etymology====
Since 1675, [[plural]] [[dative]] form of ''[[lag]]'' "law" meaning "just, right, appropriate".

===Adjective===
'''lagom'''
*[[Wiktionary:Swedish pronunciation|Pronunciation]]: {{IPAchar|/ˈlaːˌgom/}} {{Audio|sv-lagom.ogg|Audio}}
#same as the adverb
#:''Den här lägenhet är precis '''lagom''' för min dotter.''
#:"This apartment is just right for my daughter."

====Etymology====
Since 1637.

